{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "To effectively integrate AI technologies like ChatGPT into educational settings, the importance of AI literacy and prompting skills has been intensely discussed in recent research (Chiu, 2023; Denny et al., 2024; Naamati-Schneider & Alt, 2024; Stolpe & Hallström, 2024).",
    "AI literacy can be defined as understanding AI fundamentals, applications, and ethical considerations, enabling users to engage responsibly with AI systems.",
    "On the other hand, prompting skills infer writing clear, specific, and context-rich inputs to get accurate and relevant responses from AI.",
    "The previous research has revealed that users with a solid understanding of AI and adept prompting abilities can better harness the capabilities of ChatGPT, leading to more productive and meaningful interactions (Knoth et al., 2024).",
    "Besides, AI-literate users can communicate more effectively with ChatGPT, resulting in higher quality responses (Tzirides et al., 2024)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "To effectively integrate AI technologies like ChatGPT into educational settings, the importance of AI literacy and prompting skills has been intensely discussed in recent research (Chiu, 2023; Denny et al., 2024; Naamati-Schneider & Alt, 2024; Stolpe & Hallström, 2024).",
    "The previous research has revealed that users with a solid understanding of AI and adept prompting abilities can better harness the capabilities of ChatGPT, leading to more productive and meaningful interactions (Knoth et al., 2024).",
    "Besides, AI-literate users can communicate more effectively with ChatGPT, resulting in higher quality responses (Tzirides et al., 2024)."
  ]
}